### Test: Standard Response without API Version
# Estimate token usage based on your request content; compare your estimates against the X-Prompt-Tokens, X-Completion-Tokens, and X-Total-Tokens response headers.
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: api-key
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-responses-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2025-03-01-preview
# UAIG-API-Type: responses 
# UAIG-Model-ID: gpt-4.1-mini
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /openai/responses
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/responses
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
    "input": "Explain the concept of API versioning in software development",
    "temperature": 0.3
}

###

### Test: Responses API with Streaming
# This test validates Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming for the Responses API
# 
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: api-key
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-responses-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2025-03-01-preview
# UAIG-API-Type: responses 
# UAIG-Model-ID: gpt-4.1-mini
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /openai/responses
# UAIG-Is-Streaming: true
# UAIG-Request-Timeout: 360 (120 base * 3 streaming multiplier)
#
# Expected Streaming Response Validation:
# 1. Response Headers: Content-Type should be "text/event-stream" with Transfer-Encoding: chunked
# 2. Response Body: Multiple "data:" prefixed JSON chunks arriving incrementally
# 3. Stream terminates with: data: [DONE]
#
# NOTE: The complete response is distributed across all chunks. Concatenate the content 
# values from each chunk to reconstruct the full response text.
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/responses
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
    "input": "Say goodbye in 5 words.",
    "temperature": 0.3,
    "stream": true
}

###

### Test: Standard Response
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: api-key
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-responses-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2025-03-01-preview (overwrites provided version in requestwith value in metadata-config)
# UAIG-API-Type: responses 
# UAIG-Model-ID: gpt-4.1-mini
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /openai/responses
# @name stdResponse
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/responses?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
    "input": "Write a creative haiku about cloud computing and AI integration",
    "temperature": 0.8
}

### Extract the response ID from the Standard Response test
@stdResponseId = {{stdResponse.response.body.id}}

###

### Test: Chained Response with Context (using previous_response_id)
# This test demonstrates how to chain responses together while maintaining context
# The model will have full context of the previous question and response without manually including it
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: api-key
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-responses-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2025-03-01-preview
# UAIG-API-Type: responses 
# UAIG-Model-ID: gpt-4.1-mini
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /openai/responses
# NOTE: Run the "Standard Response" test above first to get a valid response ID
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/responses?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
    "previous_response_id": "{{stdResponseId}}",
    "input": "Can you explain that in simpler terms that a high school student would understand?"
}

###

### Test: Get Response (GET) - Standard API with API Version
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: api-key
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-responses-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2025-03-01-preview  (overwrites provided version in requestwith value in metadata-config)
# UAIG-API-Type: responses 
# UAIG-Model-ID: not-applicable
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /openai/responses/{responseId}
# NOTE: If a response with the specified ID doesn't exist, you will receive a 404 response
GET {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/responses/{{stdResponseId}}?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Test: Delete Response (DELETE) - Standard API without API version
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Auth-Type: api-key
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-responses-backend
# UAIG-Selected-API-Version: 2025-03-01-preview
# UAIG-API-Type: responses 
# UAIG-Model-ID: not-applicable
# UAIG-Forwarded-Path: /openai/responses/{responseId}
# NOTE: If a response with the specified ID doesn't exist, you will receive a 404 response
DELETE {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/responses/{{stdResponseId}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

